cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.CR 

This paper uses data from Twitter to study the antecedents of ISIS support, which involves natural language processing and social network analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves classification of Arabic tweets, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The study also looks at temporal patterns, which could be categorized under cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) or cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy). Finally, the paper discusses the violent acts of ISIS, which could be classified under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
